        },
        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Bridge Import Walkthrough\n\nThis lesson explains the current truth behind legend-style creation entries:\n\n- the entries are derived\n- bridge import supplies starter authority\n- the catalog graph provides the class targets"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "legend-type-walkthrough-step-1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": 100,
        "y": -980
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-bridge-import-walkthrough"
        },
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Build A Catalog\n\nIn one graph, place bridge nodes that target node classes.\n\nThat catalog is where the starter data lives."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "legend-type-walkthrough-step-2",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": 600,
        "y": -980
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-bridge-import-walkthrough"
        },
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Import The Catalog\n\nIn the consumer graph, add a bridge that points at the catalog graph and grants `create`.\n\nThat import is what lets creation affordances discover the class entries."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "legend-type-walkthrough-step-3",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 3",
      "position": {
        "x": 1100,
        "y": -980
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-bridge-import-walkthrough"
        },
        "markdown": "## Step 3: Verify Discovery\n\nOpen the consumer graph and confirm that the imported entries can be discovered and used.\n\nThe bridge gives authority to create from the supplied starter data."
      }
    },
